# narrator.wyoming configuration — EXAMPLE.
#
# Copy this to `config/narrator.wyoming` (which is gitignored) and edit for your
# network:
#     cp config/narrator.wyoming.example config/narrator.wyoming
#
# Used in two places:
#   - Host builds (wyomingtest / saytest): host, port, runs, text, voice.
#   - On-target: the boot script copies it to ENV:narrator.wyoming, which
#     narrator.device reads at runtime (nw_read_prefs) for host/port and the
#     sex -> Piper-voice mapping. Nothing is baked into the binary.
#
# On the Amiga, ENV: is in RAM and rebuilt from ENVARC: at boot, so to keep your
# settings across reboots save the file to BOTH, e.g.:
#     Copy ENV:narrator.wyoming ENVARC:narrator.wyoming
#
# Format: "key value" per line; lines starting with # or ; are comments.

# --- Piper Wyoming server (required) ---
host 192.168.1.50          # <-- your Piper/Wyoming server IP or hostname
port 10200                 # Wyoming Piper default

# --- Voice mapping (optional) ---
# Piper voice names; each MUST exist on your server (the names below are common
# Piper voices, shown as examples). `sex` is set at runtime by the caller (e.g.
# Say's -m / -f, via narrator_rb.sex); these keys only say which Piper voice
# each sex maps to. Omit all three to use the server's default voice.
#
# NOTE: voice choice affects articulation. Say with no flag uses MALE (DEFSEX),
# so voice_male is your everyday voice. Some voices clip final consonants on
# short isolated words (e.g. en_US-ryan-high renders "test" as ~"tess"); pick a
# clearly-articulating voice for voice_male. en_US-lessac-medium is a safe bet.
voice         en_US-lessac-medium    # default / fallback voice
voice_male    en_US-lessac-medium    # used when narrator_rb.sex == MALE (Say's default)
voice_female  en_US-amy-medium       # used when narrator_rb.sex == FEMALE

# --- AHI audio mode (optional) ---
# AHI mode ID (AHIA_AudioID) to play through. Default 0x0002000f is paula
# HiFi 14 bit mono calibrated -- the highest-quality paula mono mode and the
# right portable default for real hardware. On Amiberry, the emulator-specific
# drivers measure cleaner per docs/audio-capture-rig.md:
#   0x003b0002   uaesnd: HiFi Stereo
#   0x001a0000   UAE 16 bit HIFI Stereo++
# Pick whichever is configured in your AHI prefs as your music-app mode. Hex
# (0x...) or decimal both work. The device reopens AHI on the new mode at the
# next CMD_WRITE if you change this at runtime.
audio_mode 0x0002000f

# --- Output level / headroom (optional) ---
# AHI output level as a percent of full scale (1..100; default 80). Piper's PCM
# peaks reach 0 dBFS, and AHI's resample to the Paula/output rate overshoots
# those full-scale peaks, which clips and sounds harsh/distorted on loud
# syllables. Keeping this below 100 leaves headroom so peaks don't hit the
# ceiling. 80 is a good default; lower it (e.g. 70) if loud peaks still distort,
# raise it toward 100 for maximum loudness if your output stays clean.
gain 80

# --- PCM capture (optional, for audio-quality investigation) ---
# When set to an AmigaDOS path, the device also writes a WAV copy of the raw
# little-endian PCM Wyoming sent us (no per-utterance silence pre-roll, only
# actual data). Format mirrors Wyoming's: 22050Hz / 16-bit / mono. Spans one
# device session (OpenDevice..CloseDevice); overwritten each open. Empty (or
# omitted) = capture off. Useful target: Narrator:capture.wav (lands in the
# repo root on the host via the Amiberry mount). Off by default. See
# docs/audio-capture-rig.md for how to A/B against a BlackHole loopback
# recording of the speaker-out.
# capture Narrator:capture.wav

# --- Latency: split long input into pipelined chunks (optional) ---
# Piper synthesizes one SENTENCE at a time, so a single long sentence has to be
# fully rendered before any audio starts (e.g. ~2.3s for a 40-word run-on).
# Multi-sentence text already starts fast. Set split_words > 0 to break the text
# into chunks of about this many words (at sentence -> clause -> word
# boundaries) and pipeline them, so the FIRST chunk starts in ~250ms; the rest
# synthesize while it plays, so playback stays gapless. Small prosody cost at the
# split points. 0 (or omitted) = off: send the whole text in one request (most
# natural). A value around 12-20 is a good start.
split_words 0

# --- Host-build-only knobs (ignored by the device) ---
runs 3                     # wyomingtest: repeat count
text Hello from the Amiga. This is neural speech over Wyoming.
